## Phase 3: Relocate Entity Detail, Navigation Cleanup, and Delete Old Directory

### Overview

Move the entity detail page from `/{slug}/entities/[entityId]` to `/{slug}/entity/[entityId]` (singular), update AppSidebar and command palette links, and delete the old `entities/` directory — all in one pass to avoid a window of duplication.

### Changes Required:

#### 1. Entity Detail Layout (new location)

**File**: `apps/app/src/app/(app)/(org)/[slug]/(manage)/entity/[entityId]/layout.tsx` (new)
**Changes**: Copy from existing `entities/[entityId]/layout.tsx`, add `RealtimeProviderWrapper` (previously inherited from parent entities layout)

```tsx
import { HydrateClient, prefetch, trpc } from "@repo/app-trpc/server";
import { RealtimeProviderWrapper } from "@repo/app-upstash-realtime/client";

export default async function EntityDetailLayout({
  children,
  params,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  params: Promise<{ entityId: string }>;
}) {
  const { entityId } = await params;

  prefetch(trpc.entities.get.queryOptions({ externalId: entityId }));
  prefetch(
    trpc.entities.getEvents.infiniteQueryOptions(
      { externalId: entityId, limit: 20 },
      { getNextPageParam: (lastPage) => lastPage.nextCursor ?? undefined }
    )
  );

  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <RealtimeProviderWrapper>{children}</RealtimeProviderWrapper>
    </HydrateClient>
  );
}
```

Note: The existing entity detail layout at `entities/[entityId]/layout.tsx` did NOT include `RealtimeProviderWrapper` — it inherited from the parent `entities/layout.tsx`. Since the new location is directly under `(manage)`, it needs its own `RealtimeProviderWrapper` for the `useRealtime` hook in `EntityDetailView`.

